        "rtf_4wHnU8": {
          "type": "rtf",
          "settings": {
            "richtext_content": "<h3>Career Highlights</h3><p><strong>Fight Record<br/></strong>15 fights - 15 wins - 10 KOs.</p><p><strong>2019 <br/></strong>Callum made his professional boxing debut against Elvis Dube winning a points decision. </p><p><strong>2022<br/></strong>Callum had four fights. Winning all by TKO against Michal Gazdik, Michal Loniewski, Farouk Daku, and won his first title by defeating Ben Ridings to win the Central Area super middleweight title.</p><p><strong>2023<br/></strong>Making his Boxxer debut in March 2023 against Celso Neves,winning via TKO. In July, Simpson beat Boris Crighton via unanimous decision. The third fight of the year came against Jose de Jesus Macias, with Simpson winning via unanimous decision after scoring a knockdown in the eighth round.</p><p><strong>2024<br/></strong>3rd August 2024, in his hometown of Barnsley at the Oakwell Football Ground, Callum fought Zak Chelli and won to become the British and Commonwealth super middleweight champion.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
