    "content_rich_text_AkP8W8": {
      "type": "content-rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "rtf_dMkYVt": {
          "type": "rtf",
          "settings": {
            "richtext_content": "<p>Callum’s journey to becoming a top contender in the boxing world hasn’t been easy, but his dedication and focus have pushed him through every challenge. He’s committed to inspiring others, showing that with the right mindset, anything is possible.</p><p>Before pursuing a career in boxing, Callum was a keen footballer, playing for Sheffield & Hallamshire County Senior League Premier Division side, Dodworth Miner's Welfare F.C. where his Dad was manager.</p><p>He left at the age of eight before taking up boxing in Bolton upon Dearne, Barnsley, later moving to train at Barnsley Star Boxing Club under Trevor Schofield.</p><p>He had 53 amateur fights, winning 38 before turning professional in 2019.</p><p>Discover Gym King Fight Division, Callums go-to that keeps him at the top of his game, from grueling training sessions to downtime.</p>"
          }
        }
